DTC detecting condition
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Trouble area
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
DTC P0722: Output Speed Sensor Circuit No Signal
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
This DTC is detected if any one of the following conditions is met.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Vehicle speed signal is lower than specified value even if secondary pulley speed signal is higher than specified value.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Output signal value of vehicle speed sensor is lower than half of the actual vehicle speed for specified time.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<ptxt>
(1 D/C detection logic)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Vehicle speed sensor and/or its circuit
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
TCM
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</servinfosub>
